# Cart Rave — Design Document / Project Bible

## What this project is
Cart Rave — a browser-based multiplayer physics sumo game entered into the Cursor Vibe Jam 2026.
Shopping carts on a giant spinning vinyl record in a nightclub setting. Last cart on the record wins. Short rounds, instant respawn, intentionally janky physics. The name is a nod to the Crab Rave meme, and the whole thing is meant to be dumb in a way that makes people want to send clips to friends.

Pitch: "Cart Rave. Sumo on a spinning turntable. Last cart at the afterparty."
Tonal references: Halo Sumo (Warthogs on Sandtrap) + Gorillaz Final Drive flash game + Crab Rave energy.

## Stack
- Three.js (rendering)
- Rapier3D (physics)
- PartyKit or Colyseus (multiplayer if stretch)
- Supabase (leaderboard)
- Vercel (hosting)
- Single domain: cartrave.lol

## Jam Rules (CRITICAL)
- MANDATORY widget in HTML: <script async src="https://vibej.am/2026/widget.js"></script>
- 90%+ AI-generated code
- Browser-playable, no login, no loading screens (instant load required)
- Free to play, single domain
- Deadline: May 1, 2026 @ 13:37 UTC

## What players should feel
Disbelief, chaos, "I need to show someone this," satisfaction from a good ram, Crab Rave victory energy when they win.

## Core loop
Spawn on rotating turntable with up to 7 other carts → 30-60 seconds of ramming and surviving → fall off = ragdoll into void → last cart wins round → music stinger → instant respawn.

## Core verb
Push. No weapons, no power-ups, no abilities. Physics + positioning = all skill expression.

## Arena
Giant vinyl record spinning slowly (0.5-1 rotation per round). Center label is safest, edges are deadly. Floats in neon-lit club space — DJ booth background, strobes, fog, colored spotlights. Not full club interior, not pure void.

## Vehicle
Stock shopping cart. Stretch: 3-4 cosmetic variants including a crab-driven cart as rare/hidden.

## Controls
- WASD/arrows to drive
- Space for horn (no mechanical effect, pure comedy button)
- Nothing else

## Round structure
One cart remaining OR 60-second timer (cart closest to center wins on timeout). Running session tally, no match end.

## Visual direction
Low-poly with modern lighting. Neon rave palette: hot pink, electric blue, lime green, UV purple. Strobes and color cycling but not seizure-inducing. Chunky readable shapes. Intentionally janky animations — the jank is the point.

## Audio direction
- One main track (Crab Rave-adjacent original loop, steel drum energy)
- Bass-reactive visual elements
- Bicycle-horn-pitched-up for the horn SFX
- Long Wilhelm-adjacent ragdoll scream on death
- Airhorn + cheering on victory

## Personality details
- Ragdoll ejection on death
- Spammable horn with no cooldown
- Title screen "CART RAVE" in club-poster font with tagline "like crab rave but with carts"
- Fake 16/32 bit color toggle (does nothing, Final Drive homage)
- Hidden void hole somewhere on record
- One cart skin is a crab

## Scope tiers

### MUST SHIP (MVP)
- One arena, one cart, single-player survival mode
- Rotating platform, fall detection, respawn
- Core physics feel nailed
- Horn button
- Basic lighting and music
- Personal-best leaderboard
- Vibe Jam widget deployed
- Deployed to cartrave.lol

### SHOULD SHIP (stretch 1)
- Multiplayer (2-4 min, 8 ideal)
- Ragdoll death animation
- Multiple cart skins
- Title screen polish with meme jokes

### NICE TO HAVE (stretch 2)
- Crab cart unlockable
- Music rotation
- Hidden void hole
- Mobile support
- Fake bit-depth toggle
- Between-round song voting

## Non-goals (will NOT build)
Story mode, campaign, progression systems, unlocks that gate gameplay, microtransactions, accounts/logins, custom arenas, anything taking >30min to add during final week.

## Key constraints for AI coding
- Instant load is a hard constraint — no splash screen, no preloader, no click-to-start
- Lazy-load all assets, no big upfront bundle
- Widget script must be in index.html at all times
- Single file or minimal bundled setup preferred
- Physics tuning is highest priority — cart feel is the game
- Keep scope tight, do not add features not listed above
